title: For Sale:  Browning 92 .44 Mag. Lever Action Saddle Gun
postcontent:
Browning Model 92 Lever Action .44 magnum
Very good condition. 20” barrel.
Comes with original box (which is a bit rough) with all packing materials, owner's manual and warranty card showing original purchase date of April 1982.
I decided to refinish the stock some years ago and after I got it stripped and saw how pretty the wood was (IMO) I elected to not re-stain it but just finished it with about 6 coats of Linspeed oil (which if you've even used it is pretty labor intensive). If someone wanted to return it to factory-spec original dark brown it would be trivial and all of the prep work has been done.
There is an area about ½” wide at the midpoint of the barrel on top where the bluing shows wear. No idea what caused that. Also the little notched ramp for elevation adjustment of the rear sight is missing. It was like that when I got it and I never bothered with it. I just looked and the notched ramps are available on Midway website For $1.99.
I've had this rifle about 10 years and have probably put 50 rounds through it. Does nothing but sit and I'm not getting any younger so someone else might as well enjoy it. Price is firm and if you look at what they are selling for on sites like Gun Broker I think you will agree it is fair. I guess these have become sort of collectible as they were only made for 8 years. I've even seen the little manual alone listed for $35.
